    <p id="tribute-title">Chester's Life</p>
    <ul>
      <li>March 20, 1976 â€“ July 20, 2017</li>
      <li>Best known for his role as the lead vocalist of Linkin Park.</li>
      <li>His early childhood life was not a pleasant one at all, from sexual abuse to family seperation and getting into drugs to cope with everything.</li>
      <li>Started his musical career around the age of 18 with some of his friends in phoenix, arizona.</li>
      <li>After some time he left the band but couldn't find a new one and was ready to quit until he got called from Jeff Blue to audition for a new band that would become Linkin Park. </li>
      <li>There was problems starting up the band but after those problems got fixed the band became what it is today.</li>
      <li>Chester died on July 20, 2017 due to suicide, speculation believes it to be because of depression.</li>
  </ul>
